data.description: Welcome to your newly renovated  (2020) and stunning 2000+ sqft home nestled in the enchanting Kingsessing/Squirrel Park neighborhood of Philadelphia.  Boasting three bedrooms and 2.5 baths, this meticulously cared-for home is ready to be your dream abode.  The expansive first level welcomes you with an open layout, seamlessly blending functionality with the perfect atmosphere for entertaining featuring gorgeous hardwood flooring, recessed lighting, and an abundance of natural light.  The eat-in kitchen is a culinary haven, showcasing custom cabinets, quartz countertops, an under-counter built-in microwave, a ventless hood, and sleek black stainless steel appliances. The enclosed porch, currently used as a piano studio, offers versatility as a charming home garden or office space.  Ascend to the second level to discover three generously sized bedrooms with ample closet space, including a master bedroom with a full ensuite bath for your convenience and privacy.  The finished basement is a versatile space with a bespoke glass wine cellar and storage areas that can be tailored to your preferences. There's also the potential to create a bonus room for guests.  Step outside to the rear deck, providing a picturesque, unobstructed view of the Philadelphia skyline. The fenced yard, offering tranquility and privacy, is an idyllic space for hosting events.  This residence is a rare find in the thriving and sought-after community it resides in and  just a short walk to everything the area has to offer.  Just a few blocks to Clark Park, the heart of West Philly, with a weekly farmers' market, festivals, youth soccer and more.  Also just a few blocks away from Kingsessing Rec Center, which is currently undergoing a $25 million renovation.  Close to Baltimore Avenue, shopping and restaurants,  including a brand new Indian restaurant and a Vietnamese cafe.  Short 15-20 min drive to Center City and the Philadelphia Airport.  The seller is offering a one-year AHS Home Warranty with an accepted offer.  Inquire about the possibility of assuming this home's FHA assumable low-interest mortgage and how you may qualify for up to $18,000 in down payment and closing cost assistance.  Don't miss out on this extraordinary opportunity.  Make your appointment to see it urban gem today!
